<td align="center">
<div class="poemtitle">The Flat Hand of Winter</div> 
<br>
<a class="byline" href="javascript:goauthor('goodwin')">by Jude Goodwin</a> <br>
<br>
<br>
<table cellpadding="20" cellspacing="0"><tr><td>
A passing neighbour waves his white hand<BR>
as if lifting a fish. The roadways are thick<BR>
with its scales and shine<BR>
beneath a gutterless moon. The windows<BR>
weep and freeze, weep and freeze.<BR>
Even the cottonwoods<BR>
hiss as they rise from the river ice,<BR>
scrape the ceiling of night<BR>
with their brittle combs. November sulks<BR>
in a dark room with the TV flickering.<BR>
December is drinking scotch<BR>
and rubs his lips with rough fingers.<BR>
</td>
<td align="right"><img src="images/flathandofwinter.jpg"><br><span class="byartist">Patricia Wallace Jones</span></td>
</tr></table>
</td>
</tr>
